AUDIO: 'on a table in the kitchen. The can has black and white modern wavy designs to complement the logo. As a result of that, we have this cool looking zebra like styled pop can that says open art'

[14:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'with the logo. So, if you got a logo and you want to mock up a hat, a t-shirt, some product, you can do it with Flex Context. Speaking of t-shirts, that\'s exactly what I did here. And here\'s the'

[14:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'cool thing about this model. We can take everything we\'ve learned and iterate every step of the way. So, we\'ve already gone from logo to t-shirt. And now with the reference image as the t-shirt, we'

[14:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can prompt for a woman wearing it with jeans walking in the city. You don\'t even need a model. And as a result, I have a woman here wearing the open art t-shirt and jeans. Oh, but wait, there\'s'

[14:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'more. We could take that same image of the woman wearing the open art t-shirt as a reference. And now I want her to wear a blue dress playing the violin at'

[15:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a concert. Notice how it keeps the likeness of her face. She\'s now wearing a blue dress in a totally different composition. Oh, you say that maybe she\'s lonely and she needs a boyfriend.'

[15:18] [scene:talk]
